(13, 'History Pride month', 'Lorraine Hansberry (1930 ''-''1965) was a playwright, writer, and activist. Her play, “A Raisin in the Sun” (1959), was the first drama by an African American woman produced on Broadway...', 'https://res.cloudinary.com/dldvfnn89/image/upload/v1686573591/352233145_238700062215585_447367495220412331_n_Small_hoi0fo.png','es'),
(14, 'Juneteenth Food','Happy June "Juneteenth Food Traditions with Hue Williams," a 5-part series, continues this week at Baisley Park. Hue Williams, a food historian focusing on the intersectionality of foodways within the African diaspora, will lead a presentation about food and cooking traditions connected to Juneteenth. Participants will have time to share stories about their special dishes and will take a keepsake recipe card home. The series continues throughout June at different library branches in Queens. Please check our events calendar to learn more: https://buff.ly/3MrPy1y', 'https://res.cloudinary.com/dldvfnn89/image/upload/v1686573773/351527784_244124618259661_7859850632306906783_n_Small_hsmxj6.png','tl'),
(15, 'Fight rent increase','Queens neighbors, is your monthly rent overwhelming? Is the possibility of owning your own home completely out of reach? Are you fed up with $ being spent on luxury apartments instead of affordable housing? Queens is becoming unaffordable and THE TIME IS NOW TO TAKE ACTION. We are demanding that the state-owned land at Creedmoor in eastern Queens be used to provide 1,000 new affordable rental units and 300 affordable houses. Let''s fight to keep Queens inclusive! Join us for the Queens Power Rally for 100% Affordability! Sunday, June 11 at 3pm Winchester Blvd. and Union Tpke We will rally to #KeepQueensAffordable! QCH will have buses departing from Forest Hills and Jackson Heights at 2pm. Visit this link to RSVP: https://lnkd.in/eTZbC-sc','https://res.cloudinary.com/dldvfnn89/image/upload/v1686574045/347013595_791740272643782_2870552874009018896_n_Small_v7u2gb.png', 'ja'),
